SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man known only as "Marcus" to people on the street was stabbed to death 
Tuesday afternoon in front of a grocery store near 12th Avenue and Market 
Street, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The man walked into the Valu-Mart about 1:30 p.m. and collapsed by the front 
door, said Sgt. Jim Clear, a police spokesman. 
</P>
