<P>
PROFESSORS' PRIORITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The tone of Kennedy's statements and your editorial echo most recent 
discussions in implying that universities have overemphasized research in a 
self-interested pursuit of scholarly prestige and research funds. 
</P>
<P>
This may be partly true. However, it must be remembered that at present 
universities are the only institutions at which research in many fields 
(including some areas of science) can be pursued. There are few or no 
opportunities for employment in industry or in the government in these areas of 
scholarship. 
</P>
<P>
Excellent teachers can find employment in liberal art colleges, state campuses 
with a teaching emphasis, and in secondary education -- where their talents are 
sorely needed. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN DAMUTH 
</P>
