<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Telecommunications: Chicago-based Ameritech said first-quarter net income rose 
1% from a year earlier to $303.5 million, while revenue increased 5% to $2.6 
billion. The firm said results were affected by one-time expenses of about $54 
million related to work force reductions. 
</P>
<P>
GTE Corp. posted record first-quarter earnings of $355 million, a gain of 8%. 
Consolidated revenue and sales were up 9% to $4.5 billion. The Stamford, 
Conn.-based company said the results were driven by continued strong 
performance in its telephone operations and other telecommunications 
businesses. St. Louis-based Southwestern Bell Corp.'s first-quarter profit rose 
4% to $247.8 million. Revenue totaled $2.1 billion, up 4% from the same period 
a year ago. The firm attributed the increased earnings to strong growth in its 
cellular telephone division and increased access lines in its telephone 
business. United Telecommunications Inc. said first-quarter net income climbed 
41% from a year ago to $108 million. Revenue totaled $2 billion, a gain of 15%. 
The Kansas City, Mo., firm, which is the parent of US Sprint, the nation's 
third-largest long-distance carrier, attributed the results to increased 
revenue and unit volume at US Sprint. 
</P>
