<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENGLISH MUFFIN IS OK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DR. NEIL SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: Different restaurants serve different types of breads with their 
meals. 
</P>
<P>
I've even been to some restaurants that put down a tray of Danish pastry when 
you first sit down. I know that Danish is a kind of cake, so I avoid it. But 
what about an English muffin? Is that considered acceptable if you're trying to 
watch your weight? 
</P>
<P>
Answer: An English muffin is acceptable. Danish, sweet rolls and coffee cake 
are not. 
</P>
</TEXT>
