<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Celebrities Hot on Warm Earth: Daniel J. Travanti of "Hill Street Blues" 
announced plans to launch a celebrity effort to educate Americans about the 
threat of global warming. Travanti met with Mayor Tom Bradley and leaders of 
the Sierra Club on Monday to talk about the campaign, which will include a 
series of TV announcements and the distribution of global-warming action kits. 
Travanti, as well as Jane Alexander, Lloyd Bridges, Ken Olin, John Ritter and 
William Shatner, have already filmed seven public service announcements to be 
broadcast nationwide. BETH KLEID 
</P>
