<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quick, Before the Phantom Disappears: Can the sizzling black-market ticket 
prices for "Phantom of the Opera" get any hotter? Yes, if the tickets are for 
Michael Crawford's final performances. 
</P>
<P>
In one Times Classified ad Tuesday, tickets for Crawford's last date as the 
phantom on April 29 were offered at $1,500 each. Four were available, and they 
were listed as good orchestra seats. Compared to that, another ad offered 
Crawford last-day tickets at a bargain basement price, two balcony seats at 
$500 a piece. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
