<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SAN FRANCISCO; 
</P>
<P>
LAWSUIT FILED ON POLLUTION OF BAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Five environmental groups, including the Sierra Club Legal Defense Fund and 
Citizens for a Better Environment, filed suit in U.S. District Court in San 
Francisco to force the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency to impose cleanup 
rules for southern San Francisco Bay. The suit alleges that California missed a 
Feb. 4 deadline to submit "individual control strategies" required by the Clean 
Water Act for four major pollution sources -- sewage plants run by the cities 
of San Jose and Santa Clara, Palo Alto, and Sunnyvale -- as well as local storm 
drains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
