<CORRECTION>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
<P>
Hunt contribution -- The Times reported on April 18 that Texas oilman Ray Hunt 
made $17,000 in federally regulated contributions to candidates in 1988 and 
$10,000 in soft money contributions, which are not regulated by the Federal 
Election Commission. The $10,000 was not a soft money contribution, but has 
since been credited to his wife, Nancy, in FEC records. 
</P>
</CORRECTION>
