<HEADLINE>
<P>
SELES, NOW NO.3, KNOCKS OFF COLLINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LARGO, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Monica Seles celebrated her newest ranking Tuesday night with another big 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
One night after achieving a career-high No.3 world ranking, the 16-year-old 
Seles crushed qualifier Sandy Collins, 6-1, 6-1, in the Eckerd Tennis Open. 
</P>
<P>
In other matches Tuesday, sixth seeded Helen Kelesi of Canada outlasted 
Mercedes Paz of Argentina, 7-6 (7-3), 5-7, 7-6 (7-5); No.8 Susan Sloane rallied 
past Shaun Stafford, 6-4, 2-6, 7-5, and No.7 Sandra Cecchini of Italy downed 
