<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Emmons and David Reyes 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
IDENTITY CRISIS: The feds have issued a list of firms whose names sound like 
financial institutions but are not banks, trust companies or S&amp;Ls. On the 
list of sound-alikes is Great American Bank &amp; Trust in Laguna Beach, easily 
confused with the local branch of San Diego-based Great American Bank -- "the 
legitimate one," according to a federal spokesman. "Somebody is trading on 
their name." Steve Emmons and David Reyes 
</P>
</TEXT>
