CALIFORNIA IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
SACRAMENTO; 
</P>
<P>
PREGNANT POOR ARE NOT MORE LITIGIOUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pregnant patients served by the Medi-Cal program for the poor are no more 
likely to sue for malpractice than other women, an independent foundation 
reported. The Sierra Foundation, which finances local health projects in 
Northern California, said researchers compared suits against physicians by 
pregnant Medi-Cal patients to those filed by expectant mothers in the entire 
state. "Because physicians consistently cite fear of lawsuits from Medi-Cal 
patients as a top reason for refusing to serve more of this population, we 
wanted to see whether there was any validity to this perception," said Dr. 
Barbara Aved, a consultant to the foundation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
