<P>
NEWBORN HIDDEN IN PLASTIC BAG SUFFOCATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ROHNERT PARK, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-year-old girl, whose parents said they never knew she was pregnant, gave 
birth to an 8-pound boy who died after the teen-ager hid the newborn in a 
plastic bag under the bathroom sink, police said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The mother, who apparently concealed her pregnancy and gave birth in the 
bathroom of her home on Easter Sunday, lost a great amount of blood and was in 
critical condition at Santa Rosa Memorial Hospital, police said. 
</P>
<P>
After the girl was hospitalized, doctors told police to return to the family 
home to look for a baby. 
</P>
</TEXT>
