<TEXT>
<P>
Auto Sales Drop: Sales of North American-made cars and light trucks tumbled 
11.2% in early April from the incentive-boosted sales levels of the same period 
last year, auto makers said. Chrysler posted the biggest drop, with its car 
sales falling 29.2% during the April 1-10 period from a year earlier, when the 
No. 3 auto maker had just announced interest-free financing on some vehicles. 
Ford's car sales slid 20.7% and General Motors's fell 13.6% from the 
year-earlier period, the companies said. 
</P>
