</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two people were killed and two others were critically injured when a passenger 
car collided with a bobtail truck on the Golden State Freeway early this 
morning. 
</P>
<P>
A man and a woman, described as in their 30's, were pronounced dead at the 
scene, said Pat Marek, spokesman for Los Angeles Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
Their names were not released pending notification of relatives. 
</P>
<P>
The crash occurred just before 5:00 a.m. on the northbound lanes of the Golden 
State Freeway, just south of the Glendale Freeway, when the passenger car 
collided with the truck and was crushed beneath its frame, said Officer Vince 
Zambrana. It took firefighters 45 minutes to pull the two trapped victims from 
wreckage. Traffic on the heavily traveled freeway was tied up for hours at the 
height of the early-morning rush. 
